'''Charles Sinclair Butt''' (28 July 1900{{spaced ndash}}21 January 1973) was an Australian businessman. He worked for the Rapson Tyre company and the [[Dunlop Australia|Dunlop Rubber Company]]. By 1934 he was Dunlop's chief accountant.<ref>{{cite book|title=The Will to Win: The Story of Sir Frank Beaurepaire |last=Lomas |first=Graham |year=1960 |page=105 |url=https://books.google.com.sg/books?id=-MHiAAAAMAAJ }}</ref> He also served as general manager and Controller of Tyres for the Olympic Tyre & Rubber Co. Limited.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article49539441 |title=Tyre Controller |date=5 January 1943 |page=1 |newspaper=Barrier Miner }}</ref>

In 1962, he was made a Companion of the [[Order of St Michael and St George]].<ref>{{cite journal|date=25 May 1962|journal=The London Gazette|issue=42684|page=4343|title=Second Supplement to The London Gazette of Friday, 25th May 1962|url=https://www.thegazette.co.uk/London/issue/42684/page/4343|accessdate=15 April 2014}}</ref>

